  0000000me1 [II_BEG] Innovation and<br>excellence
  0000000me2 [II_BEG] My approach to programming may not be mainstream, but its freshness and uniqueness bring extraordinary results... My name is Bartłomiej Magierski and this is my portfolio.
  0000000me3 [II_BEG] Contact details
  0000000me4 [II_BEG] Every line in portfolio is written from start to finish by me, using plain but advanced JS and PHP. In my opinion, programming is like a square and a rectangle, not every programmer who knows the framework is able to program in the language in which the framework was written, but everyone who knows the base language and is able to write such a framework themselves will be able to use/understand it in full.
  0000000me5 [II_BEG] A Unique Approach
  0000000me6 [II_BEG] Strength, Beauty and Soul.
  0000000me7 [II_BEG] The beauty of programming lies in the fact that the creator is limited only by his imagination, so writing in the base language has the advantage of not being limited by the intention of the creator of the framework... of course, you can make inserts, but it affects readability, but by writing from scratch, everything is dedicated to applications, which makes it more readable, more universal and everyone can read it.
  0000000me8 [II_BEG] Writing in the base language has the advantage that you are not limited by the intention of the creator of the framework... of course, you can make inserts, but this affects readability, but when writing from scratch, everything is dedicated to the applications, which makes them more readable, more universal and everyone is in able to read it.
  0000000me9 [II_BEG] My Projects
  0000000m10 [II_BEG] A few words about the portfolio
  0000000t10 [II_BEG] Portfolio
  000000me11 [II_BEG] I see the advantages of frameworks, but for me they lack soul. If time or quantity play the most important role, the framework will definitely be justified. However, if you have a bit more time, it is worth writing something unique that will be associated only with the creator. Not just another application written with a framework, like millions of others, but someone wrote it all from a blank piece of paper himself... he must know the product, he devoted time and resources because he cared about the recipient. Reputation grows before your eyes.
  000000me12 [II_BEG] About Project
  000000me13 [II_BEG] The entire portfolio can be divided into 2 parts, the library and the projects. The library contains all files that are common to projects, so as not to copy them n times with the smallest changes. There are files and functions in the project that I could not share because they are unique to the project, and files that must be there due to Cross-origin resource sharing (this is about PHP). The latter also come originally from the library, but are copied to the project folder via the API. I didn't forget about updates, so all you need is an appropriate request sent to the "update" file to download the libraries again, and the file itself can also be updated with a query. The rest of the files from the library (JS) are downloaded from the API and loaded into the project in the form of a blob.
  000000me14 [II_BEG] When writing, I placed great emphasis on asynchrony, so that there would be as little downtime as possible caused by something downloading or something waiting for something.
  000000me15 [II_BEG] Ajax queries are moved to another thread because the browser has such a thing as a maximum number of active queries per thread. The preparation of language packs (Regexp) is moved to another thread so that the main thread does not have to wait as it is not necessary... node translation can be asynchronous. In order not to clog the CPU, the number of threads used can be limited based on the maximum number of threads.
  000000me16 [II_BEG] All traffic happens in vDOM, with minimal contact with the DOM. The name is from REACT.JS, because it fits and the operation is the same, but written by me.
  000000me17 [II_BEG] The language files are outside the HTM files, so there is only a template in the html.
